r his artistic tease, his baroque mockery, and his ironic portrayals. This unforgettable journey of discovery and creativity ranks as one of the finest stories from the pen of the irresistibly witty and insightful Gerald Vizenor.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aCreation (Literary, artistic, etc.)vFiction. 0aCreation (Literary, artistic, etc.)xFiction. 0aIndian artistsxFictionxMinnesota. 0aIndian artistszMinnesotavFiction. 4aAmerican Studies : Indigenous Studies. 4aGeneral Interest : Fiction. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143843448340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438434483423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438434483/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles